257
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:57,930
Anyway, if you hear from the Team Leader, please contact us as well.

258
00:17:57,930 --> 00:17:59,710
I understand.

259
00:18:05,690 --> 00:18:07,010
What's wrong now?

260
00:18:07,010 --> 00:18:09,790
He came looking for Team Leader Oh.

261
00:18:09,790 --> 00:18:12,130
Team Leader Oh is quite amazing.

262
00:18:12,130 --> 00:18:16,360
Another man came looking for her? Her mind was all over the place and her project even got stolen from her.

263
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:20,040
If I were her, I would just resign because I'd be so embarrassed.

264
00:18:38,890 --> 00:18:41,580
Cha Seo Hoo

265
00:19:02,090 --> 00:19:05,030
Are you even working in the same office as her now?

266
00:19:05,890 --> 00:19:07,530
Where's Ha Na?

267
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:10,250
He's looking for Ha Na.

268
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:14,030
Nice to see you today, Cha Seo Hoo.

269
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:21,000
Mind your own business. Even if I knew I wouldn't tell you.

270
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:26,060
By any chance, is Choi Won also looking for Oh Ha Na?

271
00:19:27,390 --> 00:19:29,940
It's not something you should worry about.

272
00:19:30,870 --> 00:19:32,750
You should hurry up and find her

273
00:19:32,750 --> 00:19:36,090
instead of being upset if I find her first.

274
00:19:37,460 --> 00:19:39,540
That won't be the case.

275
00:19:51,790 --> 00:19:53,270
Oh Ha Na

276
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:16,740
If you ask for a meeting right on this very day, does it mean you're not going forward with the project?

277
00:20:16,740 --> 00:20:20,130
That's not it, whether the person in charge is sick,

278
00:20:20,130 --> 00:20:21,830
or if there's something going on at home,

279
00:20:21,830 --> 00:20:23,410
she couldn't come to work today.

280
00:20:23,410 --> 00:20:26,740
Let's start the meeting once Team Leader Oh comes to work.

281
00:20:26,740 --> 00:20:29,210
Please send her straight to the concert hall.

282
00:20:29,210 --> 00:20:30,560
Today, right away is a bit—

283
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:32,820
I will be waiting.

284
00:20:32,820 --> 00:20:35,430
I will tell Team Leader Oh to go right away.

285
00:20:43,550 --> 00:20:45,000
Ah, so embarrassing!

286
00:21:13,560 --> 00:21:15,470
I am pushed out again

287
00:21:35,650 --> 00:21:39,680
by those who have accustomed themselves to each other like the air.

288
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:41,650
Every time I come close,

289
00:21:41,650 --> 00:21:45,010
I glance off the glass wall they have built.

290
00:21:49,370 --> 00:21:54,250
That day, I saw it for myself.

291
00:21:57,080 --> 00:22:01,940
Something within their hearts they themselves don't know about.

292
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:31,110
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

293
00:22:33,990 --> 00:22:35,700
Won!

294
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:45,260
Are you crazy?

295
00:22:45,260 --> 00:22:47,620
Your phone is off, I can't reach you, and you didn't even go to work.

296
00:22:47,620 --> 00:22:50,380
Do you know how worried I was?

297
00:22:50,380 --> 00:22:52,880
I was wrong.

298
00:22:54,020 --> 00:22:55,320
Are you a kid?

299
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:59,970
What are you doing, going off the radar out of the blue without even telling me anything?

300
00:22:59,970 --> 00:23:03,820
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

301
00:23:09,760 --> 00:23:12,940
I wanted to call you last night.

302
00:23:13,940 --> 00:23:18,500
But I held it in. Purposely.

303
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:37,260
That's why I got angry and left the office.

304
00:23:37,260 --> 00:23:41,610
I have no place to go aside from home, the office, and you.

305
00:23:41,610 --> 00:23:43,990
Yeah, right. That's a lie.

306
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:45,760
It's true.

307
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:48,500
Why didn't you call me then?

308
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:51,000
I'm embarrassed.

309
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:54,340
Hey, do you think there's nothing I'm embarrassed about in front of you?

310
00:23:54,340 --> 00:23:56,740
Why are you embarrassed in front of me all of a sudden?

311
00:23:56,740 --> 00:24:00,300
That great project I boasted to you about,

312
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:04,820
because this Oh Ha Na goes out of her mind because of men,

313
00:24:04,820 --> 00:24:07,680
it was taken away from me.

314
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:09,980
Don't you think I wouldn't get ashamed about it?

315
00:24:11,470 --> 00:24:15,520
Hey, something even much worse isn't embarrassing.

316
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:20,900
I am going to be independent from you.

317
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:21,840
Independence?

318
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:24,280
All this time I think I've been depending on you too much.

319
00:24:24,280 --> 00:24:26,780
Whenever I am having a hard time, you're always there.

320
00:24:26,780 --> 00:24:29,960
It has been a habit all this time, so now I can't solve anything by myself.

321
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:34,640
I get swayed here and there, and that's how I've lived so far.

322
00:24:38,300 --> 00:24:41,720
I want to practice standing up by myself.

323
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:48,000
And for the time being, men are out of my life.

324
00:24:51,220 --> 00:24:55,880
Are you talking now about me as a man, too?

325
00:24:58,220 --> 00:25:03,480
Well... just in case, as a man,

326
00:25:03,480 --> 00:25:06,580
won't you take it as you're out, too?

327
00:25:06,580 --> 00:25:11,240
Why now, of all occasions, Oh Ha Na?

328
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:12,760
I'm telling you, Won.

329
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:18,820
Even I'm just like this, I'm known in the office to be involved with a lot of men.

330
00:25:18,820 --> 00:25:22,380
It's not like I can necessarily deny that.

331
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:31,980
Hey, because of that, I couldn't be properly judged for my capabilities.

332
00:25:31,980 --> 00:25:33,900
For that, I can't forgive myself.

333
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:36,490
Team Leader Oh is really amazing.

334
00:25:36,490 --> 00:25:38,190
Another man is looking for her?

335
00:25:38,190 --> 00:25:41,920
She put her mind elsewhere and had her project taken away.

336
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:44,680
If I were her, I'd rather resign because of embarrassment.

337
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:47,840
I am going to start managing my image again.

338
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:51,600
That's why, you, Choi Won! Don't go looking for me in the office from now on.

339
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:54,300
Hey, I'm not going! You think I'll be going?

340
00:25:54,300 --> 00:25:57,200
What?Are you still angry?

341
00:25:57,200 --> 00:26:01,660
Don't think I'll let this go easily. I'm still angry.

342
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:07,400
In this case then, should I really  use this method?

343
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:10,000
Don't do it. It's not funny.

344
00:26:15,690 --> 00:26:18,250
Hey!

345
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:20,020
- Are you still angry?
- Don't do it.

346
00:26:20,020 --> 00:26:22,090
Don't do it!

347
00:26:22,090 --> 00:26:24,680
Don't do it!

348
00:26:24,680 --> 00:26:26,990
Hey! Don't do it!

349
00:26:26,990 --> 00:26:29,170
Don't do it! Please! Alright, alright!

350
00:26:29,170 --> 00:26:32,100
Don't ever go around saying you're my friend! That would really be embarrassing!

351
00:26:32,100 --> 00:26:35,640
Hey, everyone already knows you and I are a package!

352
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:37,750
Hana plus Won
( "Hana" is one in Korean, so 1 + 1)

353
00:26:39,150 --> 00:26:43,190
Hey, Oh Ha Na! If you disappear again without a word, I really won't leave you alone!

354
00:26:43,190 --> 00:26:45,810
I'm really going to be angry! Like really angry!

355
00:26:45,810 --> 00:26:48,710
When you get angry, it's really immature.

356
00:26:48,710 --> 00:26:53,090
Hey. Do you want me to show you what immaturity really is?

357
00:26:53,090 --> 00:26:54,990
Rodin. (he's doing the "The Thinker" pose)

358
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:01,010
- Frog?
- Hey, Spiderman!

359
00:27:01,010 --> 00:27:02,870
This is Spiderman!

360
00:27:02,870 --> 00:27:05,390
Behind my pain and frustration

361
00:27:05,390 --> 00:27:07,600
- Titanic!
- No! Where?

362
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:12,400
there lies, hidden like a treasure, a chance for me to always start over again.

363
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:21,900
♬ Stay by your window ♬

364
00:27:21,900 --> 00:27:25,880
The 34-year-old Oh Ha Na is still in the process of growing up.

365
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:28,200
On top of that growth curve,

366
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:31,380
she chose to push back men for now.

367
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:37,860
My heart's choice is also pushed back for a while

368
00:27:38,660 --> 00:27:42,450
to support Ha Na's choice.

369
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:47,800
I'm sorry!

370
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:49,820
It's well-known you had your work taken away.

371
00:27:49,820 --> 00:27:52,180
If a team leader doesn't listen to the Director's words,

372
00:27:52,180 --> 00:27:53,900
what do you think would become of the company's hierarchy?

373
00:27:53,900 --> 00:27:57,540
Whether it's a salary cut or a re-assignment, I'll gladly accept my punishment.

374
00:27:58,690 --> 00:28:01,430
Concentrate on the collaborative project with Cha Seo Hoo.

375
00:28:03,470 --> 00:28:06,090
Yes, I got it.

376
00:28:07,130 --> 00:28:10,020
What are you doing? Go straight to Cha Seo Hoo.

377
00:28:10,020 --> 00:28:11,600
Yes.

378
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,570
Aja aja, fighting!

379
00:28:26,570 --> 00:28:28,830
Hello, Team Leader.

380
00:28:28,830 --> 00:28:31,690
Ah, yes.

381
00:28:34,870 --> 00:28:39,230
Noona, you still haven't given me the gift certificates from last time.

382
00:28:41,270 --> 00:28:44,850
I already left it with my hoobae, so just come get it.

383
00:29:28,030 --> 00:29:30,030
Where were you?

384
00:29:30,030 --> 00:29:32,570
It's a personal matter.

385
00:29:35,870 --> 00:29:37,270
You look tired.

386
00:29:37,270 --> 00:29:41,830
I'm alright. Take a look at the poster drafts first.

387
00:29:46,730 --> 00:29:49,590
Let's have the meeting somewhere else,

388
00:29:49,590 --> 00:29:52,030
Team Leader Oh Ha Na.

389
00:30:13,430 --> 00:30:15,210
Do you want to drink?

390
00:30:49,900 --> 00:30:52,250
Where is this?

391
00:30:52,250 --> 00:30:54,610
The place where I'm staying.

392
00:30:56,230 --> 00:30:58,190
Ah, really?

393
00:30:58,190 --> 00:31:00,790
Where do I put these then?

394
00:31:02,510 --> 00:31:04,550
Just put it down wherever you deem fit.

395
00:31:05,210 --> 00:31:07,270
Over there is good.

396
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:14,910
The first draft is something we can basically use along with your concert poster.

397
00:31:14,910 --> 00:31:19,970
It gives off a warm feeling that allows you to feel it from the hard copy.

398
00:31:20,750 --> 00:31:24,110
The second draft is an image of Cha Seo Hoo the pianist.

399
00:31:24,110 --> 00:31:26,570
In order to show the warm image in the best way possible,

400
00:31:26,570 --> 00:31:30,090
it exclusively makes use of the upper body...

401
00:31:35,300 --> 00:31:36,810
Why are you stopping?

402
00:31:36,810 --> 00:31:37,850
I'm uncomfortable.

403
00:31:37,850 --> 00:31:41,490
Why? What makes you uncomfortable?

404
00:31:41,490 --> 00:31:44,530
Please say you're going to meet with me only for work purposes, Mr. Cha Seo Hoo.

405
00:31:44,530 --> 00:31:47,450
I don't mind the place, wherever it is.

406
00:31:47,450 --> 00:31:48,800
I'm okay with this hotel as well.

407
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:53,000
Just, in order for our relationship to stay strictly professional and mutually beneficial, I hope

408
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:56,730
we do our best in keeping this relationship working.

409
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:03,840
Alright. Let's do that.

410
00:32:21,150 --> 00:32:23,250
Oh, what to do? I'm sorry!

411
00:32:23,250 --> 00:32:24,860
Are you alright?

412
00:32:25,780 --> 00:32:30,290
Oh? The shoes that time... right?

413
00:32:30,290 --> 00:32:33,230
Yes! We meet again.

414
00:32:33,230 --> 00:32:35,700
Hello.

415
00:32:35,700 --> 00:32:38,450
Are you alright? I'm sorry.

416
00:32:55,370 --> 00:33:00,280
Did my sister leave something for me?

417
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:03,940
Something like gift certificates?

418
00:33:03,940 --> 00:33:07,190
Ah, right. They're in the office.

419
00:33:08,860 --> 00:33:11,260
So you're Team Leader's younger brother.

420
00:33:11,260 --> 00:33:15,690
No wonder you have really great eyes for shoe fashion.

421
00:33:15,690 --> 00:33:21,750
Ah, well. They say, as the old cock crows, the young cock learns.

422
00:33:21,750 --> 00:33:23,200
Excuse me, Dae Bak.

423
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:27,490
It's Dae Bok. Oh. Dae. Bok.

424
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:35,420
Dae Bok. By any chance, do you have a girlfriend?

425
00:33:39,850 --> 00:33:45,660
The third draft has the piano and the cymbals naturally merged into one image, and the pedal—

426
00:33:45,660 --> 00:33:47,910
What do you want to eat for dinner?

427
00:33:49,690 --> 00:33:51,790
I have to go straight to the office.

428
00:33:51,790 --> 00:33:54,390
It feels nice to hear formal Korean.

429
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:04,090
Right now, I am a marketing team leader, the representative from Tandy Shoes and in-charge of the artist.

430
00:34:04,090 --> 00:34:08,110
It is my job to ensure that you get the best conditions

431
00:34:08,110 --> 00:34:10,760
during your perfomances.

432
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:17,430
Whether this is a hotel or not,

433
00:34:18,840 --> 00:34:20,590
let's just do work.

434
00:34:25,300 --> 00:34:27,340
You look angry.

435
00:34:29,860 --> 00:34:32,160
I'll continue with the explanation.

436
00:34:38,130 --> 00:34:40,110
Over here.

437
00:34:42,500 --> 00:34:44,740
Cha Seo Hoo.

438
00:34:44,740 --> 00:34:46,630
Professor!

439
00:34:48,150 --> 00:34:49,100
Have you been well?

440
00:34:49,100 --> 00:34:52,740
Yes, Professor. What brings you here?

441
00:34:59,250 --> 00:35:03,940
Oh, Won! What time are you going to the gathering later?

442
00:35:04,610 --> 00:35:05,840
I don't know.

443
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:08,910
Hey, are you still angry?

444
00:35:08,910 --> 00:35:10,320
Yeah.

445
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:15,070
Wow, Choi Won, you subtly hold grudges.

446
00:35:16,950 --> 00:35:18,790
Oh Ha Na!

447
00:35:23,900 --> 00:35:25,710
Won!

448
00:35:27,930 --> 00:35:32,390
She's my friend from the travel club. I bought her here to introduce her to you.

449
00:35:32,390 --> 00:35:34,590
Say hello to each other.

450
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:47,740
Hey, say something! What do you not like about her?

451
00:35:47,740 --> 00:35:51,630
Instead of just sulking over there.

452
00:35:51,630 --> 00:35:53,310
You have such high standard for women.

453
00:35:53,310 --> 00:35:56,290
Hey, she was chosen the queen of the law department!

454
00:35:56,290 --> 00:35:58,550
Did I ever ask you to set me up on a date?

455
00:35:58,550 --> 00:36:02,440
Hey! You said she looked fine and that you'd like to meet her during the MT!

456
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:04,680
Hey! That, I—

457
00:36:04,680 --> 00:36:08,260
I brought her here thinking you'd like it and you'd even buy her food.

458
00:36:08,260 --> 00:36:09,450
You don't even know my good intentions.

459
00:36:09,450 --> 00:36:12,830
Hey! Still though! Do you bring just anyone to our hideout?

460
00:36:12,830 --> 00:36:14,910
Are you not thinking? Are you stupid?

461
00:36:14,910 --> 00:36:18,560
What? Stupid? Hey, Choi Won!

462
00:36:25,170 --> 00:36:27,490
Won!

463
00:36:27,490 --> 00:36:29,060
Choi Won!

464
00:36:33,550 --> 00:36:37,380
Have you had lunch? We're having lunch, let's go together!

465
00:36:39,890 --> 00:36:41,050
No, never mind.

466
00:36:41,050 --> 00:36:43,860
Why? You have time in the afternoon though.

467
00:36:43,860 --> 00:36:45,370
I'm going to the library.

468
00:36:45,370 --> 00:36:49,030
Hey, what library are you talking about right now?

469
00:36:49,030 --> 00:36:53,070
Let's go eat first before you go! Let's go!

470
00:36:54,180 --> 00:36:56,240
Sorry. I'm leaving first.

471
00:36:56,240 --> 00:37:02,000
Hey! You cheapskate! You poophead! I'm not playing with you!

472
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:06,100
Such a mull-headed person! Let's go.

473
00:37:10,380 --> 00:37:14,910
Do you remember my hard work for three whole days to have you cool off your anger back then?

474
00:37:14,910 --> 00:37:20,220
Of course! But you do know I don't just let go of my anger just because three days have passed, right?

475
00:37:20,220 --> 00:37:21,570
You have to work harder.

476
00:37:21,570 --> 00:37:27,060
Why do I feel like I'm getting spun around these days?

477
00:37:29,940 --> 00:37:34,050
Please help with the escape of other passengers.

478
00:37:34,050 --> 00:37:40,370
Alright, make a loop from both ends of the seat belt and follow along the body.

479
00:37:40,370 --> 00:37:43,370
Put one end in the buckle.

480
00:37:43,370 --> 00:37:47,210
That's right. Please pull it tighter.

481
00:37:47,210 --> 00:37:51,060
Alright. When there is a need for a supply of oxygen,

482
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:55,370
the masks will drop from the overhead compartment.

483
00:37:55,370 --> 00:38:00,470
Pull the string of the mask forward, and breathe into it a few times.

484
00:38:00,470 --> 00:38:04,840
And then place and fit it nicely with your face.

485
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:09,150
When we land, we will use...

486
00:38:15,610 --> 00:38:18,040
Hello, Sunbaenim.

487
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:21,760
Oh, Assistant Purser, it's been a while. Do we really live in one house?

488
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:24,790
That's why I'm here now.

489
00:38:24,790 --> 00:38:28,280
I heard you applied for a quick return schedule for the flights to the Americas this week.

490
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:31,390
Yeah. I have to return back quickly and protect our house.

491
00:38:31,390 --> 00:38:34,640
Are you some kind of Taekwon-V?

492
00:38:35,540 --> 00:38:37,230
Have you eaten lunch?

493
00:38:37,230 --> 00:38:39,430
Excuse me, Sunbaenim.

494
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:44,340
Can I please talk to you?

495
00:38:48,830 --> 00:38:51,090
See you at home for dinner.

496
00:38:51,090 --> 00:38:52,660
Okay.

497
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:05,830
I've thought of talking  to you as well.

498
00:39:07,410 --> 00:39:09,570
So Eun.

499
00:39:09,570 --> 00:39:10,680
Yes.

500
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:14,300
Last time, you told me I looked uneasy.

501
00:39:14,300 --> 00:39:15,950
Yes.

502
00:39:15,950 --> 00:39:18,050
I'm not uneasy.

503
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:23,900
And in the future, I hope there wouldn't be any occasion that I may hurt you.

504
00:39:26,710 --> 00:39:28,720
But, I...

505
00:39:28,720 --> 00:39:32,540
I have to go now, so see you tomorrow.

506
00:39:32,540 --> 00:39:34,160
Okay.

507
00:39:36,210 --> 00:39:38,420
See you tomorrow, Sunbaenim.

508
00:39:56,500 --> 00:39:58,410
Oh, it's you, So Eun.

509
00:40:06,390 --> 00:40:11,080
Big news, big news! It's the end, completely finished! Game over.

510
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:15,310
Is it? Looking at So Eun's expression, it doesn't seem that way.

511
00:40:15,310 --> 00:40:18,510
